narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Calc 2
Integral calculation, areas under the curve, volumes, sequences and series, convergence, limits, polar coordinates.
I learned a lot about Series, Integrals, and other important math skills that developed my arithmetic abilities.
I further developed my understanding of calculus as well as how to apply the knowledge I learned in class to outside scenarios
Mathematical analytical skills and mathematical visualization
I became more proficient in calculus concepts and learned how to solve problems without the use of a calculator.
This class really improved my studying strategies.
How to compute advanced calculus equations and problems.
I developed a better mindset as to how to approach math problems, and learned how to apply a variety of different information to solving problems.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I think the class helps you gain math maturity.
Overall, I really enjoyed this course and found little weaknesses.
I dont believe there are many weaknesses of this course. I think Professor Deithorn structured the class and the umbrella site very well.
The strengths of the course are the office hour offerings, the professors teaching style, and the structure of the course. There were no noticeable weaknesses.
I think the course is great I think the only thing I would change is the explores. I think ximera is better.
very well organized!
The professor was great, the material was well-organized, there was a good amount of content for the amount of time we had. But the explores werent the most helpful.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes even if you dont have to take it I think it helps with maturity in math.
I would. It is really well taught and there are plenty of office hours and ways to get help when needed.
Yes, this is a great course. If you did well in MATH 112 then you'll do well in this course too.
Yes, I would recommend this course to anyone who needs to take a math class, especially with Rachel.
Yes I definitely would. I think it is very well organized and facilitates student success very well.
Yes, I believe this class gives a very firm understanding of calculus which would be essential for computing multivariable problems.

Yes, if you enjoyed Calculus AB or Math 112, I would recommend taking this class. Some of the concepts can be difficult, but the professors explain them well and office hours are available if you need more one-on-one time. I enjoyed taking the course and feel like it was rewarding despite the difficulty of some concepts.
Yes. Its a great class and useful for most applications of math.
If it is with professor Diethorn, absolutely. Either way everyone should take this to have a baseline understanding or calc, but Diethorn makes the class much more enjoyable.
I would recommend this course. I learned a lot of new information, and I feel much more confident in my math skills.
